This story reminds me of a girl I used to know in school. We were 15 and even though we knew each other for two years as normal classmates. I don't know how I never noticed but one day I just realised she had cuts on her arm. Multiple long, deep, faded scars formed on her wrist to her elbow. It's actually amazing how I never noticed. And no one else asked so neither did I. We weren't close. Maybe that's why I ignored it and didn't bother asking her about it. She tended to be the highest scoring student in class and whenever I saw her in school after class, she'd be studying or reading some book. The next year, when I came back to school from the holiday break, she was no longer there. It was odd. There'd be a class gathering in the hall where the school councilor gathered us and asked us how we felt about the passing of our classmate. That's when I found out she died. I always wondered why she bothered studying if she was gonna kill herself. FYI I lied
